AGI - The two children wounded by their father in Cianciana, in Agrigentino, during a violent quarrel of man, a mechanic thirty-four years, with his wife, of Polish origins. The children, 3 and 7 years old, had been transferred to the hospital in Palermo. The wounds to the abdomen are very deep, and in particular the child has a brain hemorrhage. The man, who had barricaded himself for several hours in the house, surrendered to the carabinieri. The fact happened in a popular building. At the origin there would have been a quarrel between the two spouses, where the woman had reiterated to man the decision to want to separate.&nbsp; The violence involved the two children. &nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The woman managed to escape the stairs with her son in her arms and both were immediately rescued and taken to the hospital. The little girl was brought out of her father shortly after. The man handed her over to the rescuers climbed with a crane and then barricaded in the house. It landed on the spot to transfer the small.&nbsp; The child is admitted to pediatric Cardiosurgery at the Civic Hospital in Palermo. The baby in the intensive care of the children's hospital. The woman was also taken to the hospital but in ambulance: struck by a fendente at the abdomen, she was operated in Agrigento and is not in danger of life.
&nbsp;
The man suffered a lynching attempt by an individual who first hit with a punch the car of the carabinieri who were taking him away after the arrest and then tried to open the door that was blocked. The arbitration responded by raising the average to his address. The carabinieri blocked him and identified him. This is the last act of an afternoon of madness.&nbsp;
